### 11.3 Risk Zone 3 — Multi-feature merge (M5)

**Risk:** Dependency tracking complexity is underestimated. Two features touching overlapping paths produce integration bugs that the merge coordinator can't resolve.

**Mitigation adopted:** Explicit dependency declaration only. No auto-detection for M5.

`POST /features/:slug/dependsOn/:otherSlug` (via orchestrator-api, Manager-authority required). Stored in lifecycle-management SQLite as `(feature, depends_on_feature, declared_at)`. M5 merge rule: feature B cannot enter Phase 5 (Deployment) until every feature in `B.dependsOn` has Phase 7 = passed. Auto-detection via path-overlap analysis is explicitly **out of scope for M5**; stretch goal for M7+.

This keeps M5 buildable. Auto-detection is a research problem (path-overlap ≠ semantic conflict); explicit declaration is a CRUD problem.

**M5 task list addition:** Implement `POST /features/:slug/dependsOn/:otherSlug` endpoint in `orchestrator-api` with Manager-authority check. Add `feature_dependencies` table to lifecycle-management SQLite. Update MergeCoordinator to query dependencies before allowing Phase 5 entry.

