### 11.4 Design Call 1 — Phase 7 backtrack target

**Resolved in §11.2 Fix A.** Phase 7 does not backtrack. It blocks and waits for Manager intervention. Rationale: a retrospective failure is a process gap, not a code defect — re-running Implementation won't fix a missing retrospective.

### 11.5 Design Call 2 — Test isolation strategy

**Resolved in §11.1.** Two-tier: scoped tests (Tier 1, under lock, <5s budget for git ops only — tests moved to Tier 2) and full suite (Tier 2, async post-commit on worktree clone with `TestFailed` → revert). The existing M3 code at §6.2 must be refactored: remove `runWorktreeValidation` from the locked block; move it to an async post-commit handler.

### 11.6 Design Call 3 — Heartbeat tuning

**Resolved: configurable, calibrated defaults, validated post-M2.**

| Param | Env var | Default | Source |
|-------|---------|---------|--------|
| Interval | `HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS` | 30000 | Estimated |
| Stall threshold | `HEARTBEAT_STALL_MS` | 90000 | Estimated (3 × interval) |

Post-M2 load test: run 10 concurrent agents × 5-minute turns, measure P99 heartbeat-delivery latency under bus load. Adjust stall threshold to `3 × interval + P99_jitter`. Document the final values in `orchestrator/infra/redis-keyspaces.md` as "calibrated, not theoretical". Until then, defaults are estimates — flag this in the M2 verification checklist.

### 11.7 Design Call 4 — Planned-gaps approval authority

**Resolved: two-stage authority.**

| Stage | Who | Token required? | Effect |
|-------|-----|-----------------|--------|
| **Declaration** (per-phase, path c) | Agent | No | Phase exits; gap recorded in progress report |
| **Review** (Phase 7 gate) | Manager | Yes — to **reject** | Rejection forces backward intent to the originating phase; acceptance is the default |

This matches designer2's spec exactly: declaration is routine and free (keeps ambition cheap); rejection is the gated exception. The Manager token is checked by `agent-registry` at Phase 7 review, not at declaration time. Per-phase declaration never blocks on Manager availability.

### 11.8 Design Call 5 — Multi-feature dependency heuristics

**Resolved in §11.3.** Explicit API only for M5: `POST /features/:slug/dependsOn/:otherSlug`. Auto-detection deferred to M7+. Product scoping: M5 ships with manual dependency declaration; if users complain post-launch, M7 adds path-overlap hints as a non-blocking suggestion, never as an enforced rule.

